list.comment: UPDATE: 11/14/2015 Kenny Cauthen Changes made to gamecontroller 2 and Game. Game load method now a contructor. Need to Initial menu system implemented. Fixed my classes where they were pointing to null. Fixed puzzleArrayListGenerator algorithm. Removed all static reference and fixed static exceptions. WILLDO: Finish up Unit Testing for PuzzleClass and Planet Class.

option.name: myStatusName
option.value: Will be merged with property conflicts

task.summary: Planet Class is pretty much done. It provides the attributes and methods for Planet objects. I created a separate class named PlanetMaker that will contain all the String Messages for Name, explore message, scan message, and arrival message as arrays. It will also contain all the predefined Planet objects added into a planetArrayList which is added at the top of GameController. Only attribute that is allowed to be modified is if the boolean of whether or not a planet has been explored. I also changed a few attributes of planets. Instead of having booleans for whether it is a gasplanet, bossplanet, or specialPlanet(Created a doc file with descriptions) I created another int flag notation since there was no case where two of these existed at the same time.

UPDATE: 11/7/2015 Planet Class, Puzzle Class, and Dice Class are all completed. PlanetMaker Class and PuzzleMaker Class are structurally completed. Just need to insert actually message descriptions. However, all my classes should be testable. I created a few test Puzzles that are integrated to three Planets as well. I created another class called Dice which the constructor takes in percent chance of hitting with a method called roll that return a Boolean. Fixed GameController items that were related to puzzle or planet objects. Added some notes to both Captain and Enemy where they should both extend Persona. . . Also Enemy and Captain both have names so that should also go into Persona, instead of having setCaptain name and setEnemy Name.
UPDATE: 11/9/2015 Kenny Cauthen Minor Changes. Added boolean flag for if planet has been explored to Planet class. Some minor edits to clean up code in Puzzle and PuzzleMaker Class.
UPDATE: 11/9/2015 Kenny Cauthen Minor Changes. Sample Menu Item for Starter screen at bottom of GamController
